      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/25/434",
      "text": [
        " اَلسَّفَرِ وَ هُوَ مَعَ اَلْمُسْلِمِينَ فَيَمُوتُ قَالَ «لاَ يُغَسِّلُهُ مُسْلِمٌ وَ لاَ يَدْفِنُهُ وَ لاَ كَرَامَةَ وَ لاَ يَقُومُ عَلَى قَبْرِهِ وَ إِنْ كَانَ أَبَاهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.434 - The Imam was asked about a Christian who dies while traveling among Muslims.\nImam (as) said: \"A Muslim should not wash him, nor bury him, nor give him any honor, and should not stand by his grave, even if he was his father.\""
        ]
      }
    },
